In entry 17 a stillbirth is denoted as: `17, Ein todtgeboren Tochter`.

=== Idiosyncracies of Petzen Scribes

In the Petzen church registers often the Kurrent "h" is perplexingly used for "s"; for example, in the spelling of `Jobst Heinrich Krückeberg` in his
xref:petzen$vol2-image5.adoc#jobst-heinrich-kruckeberg-1790[1790 marriage entry] as `Jobht Heinrich Krückeberg`.

=== Horizontal Line above a letter

The horizontal line written above a letter (most often consonants) means the letter should be doubled. The line above the **n** in `Waterman` below
means double the n: `Watermann`. In this case, it saved the scribe space as he encountered the right edge of the page. 

