[TIP]
.The sound of ÿ
====
On page 19 of   _Deciphering Handingwriting in German Documents_, Dr. Roger Minert explains ÿ is a vowel not a consonant:

 "Essentially non-existant as a consonant in German, this character has two main vowel
functions..."

.The two vowel sounds of ÿ
1. The sound of the dipthong `ei` or `ai` as in `Loreleÿ`.
2. When written after a consonant, it is pronounced as **ü** as in Sylke = pass:[<span style="font-family: '18th Century Kurrent Text'; font-size: 2em;">Sylke</span>] or as the "ee" sound in _Eggly_. 
